
1. How Swimm Produces Documentation (Internal Working)

Swimm does not “write docs from text”.
It builds a structured knowledge model of the repository first.

1.1 Repository Ingestion (Local Analysis)
What happens

Swimm scans the entire COBOL repository locally

No cloud upload (important for enterprise systems)

It collects:

.cbl / .cob files

Program boundaries

COPYBOOK usage

Entry points

CALL statements

File I/O operations

Control structures (IF, PERFORM, EVALUATE)

Output

A raw structural index of the codebase.

Think of this as “indexing before understanding”.

1.2 COBOL Parsing & Static Analysis

Swimm uses language-aware static analysis, not regex.

It builds:

AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) for each program

Symbol tables (variables, records, files)

Control Flow Graph (CFG)

Call Graph (program → program)

Why this matters

This enables:

Accurate diagrams

Line-level linking

Program responsibility detection

1.3 Knowledge Base Construction (Core Step)

All extracted data is merged into a Knowledge Base (KB).

KB contains:

Programs as nodes

Sections & paragraphs as sub-nodes

Calls & data flows as edges

File and DB interactions

Entry → exit paths

Conceptually:

Program A
 ├─ Section X
 │   ├─ Paragraph P
 ├─ CALL → Program B
 └─ READ → CUSTOMER-FILE


⚠️ This KB is the single source of truth.

1.4 Semantic Grouping (Module & Sub-Module Detection)

Using the KB, Swimm identifies:

Logical groupings of programs

Menu-driven programs

Business logic clusters

Utility programs

Techniques used

Call frequency analysis

Entry-point clustering

Naming patterns

Data access similarity

Result

Suggested modules & sub-modules, exactly like you saw in the video.

1.5 AI-Assisted Explanation Layer

Now AI is applied on top of structured data (important).

AI does:

Convert program logic → natural language

Explain intent, not syntax

Generate walkthroughs

Because AI reads:

AST + CFG

Not raw COBOL text

This avoids hallucination.

1.6 Markdown Document Generation

From the KB + AI explanations, Swimm generates .md files.

Each document includes:

Headings

Text explanations

Code references

Diagram placeholders

Metadata (file, line numbers)

Example metadata (hidden):

program: customer_menu.cbl
section: MAIN-PARA
lines: 120–210

2. How Swimm Displays the Documentation (UI + Interaction)

This is where your feature requirements come alive.

2.1 IDE-Embedded Markdown Renderer

Docs are rendered inside VS Code

Looks like normal Markdown

But enhanced with IDE commands

Why this matters

No context switching

Developers trust IDE-native tools

2.2 Interactive Overview Document
What is shown

Repository description

Major modules

High-level diagrams

How it works

Each module name is a clickable reference

Clicking updates:

Center panel (doc)

Diagram focus

This is stateful Markdown, not static.

2.3 Diagram Generation & Display
How diagrams are produced

From the KB:

Call graph → component diagram

CFG → flow diagram

Dependency graph → architecture diagram

Rendered using:

SVG / Mermaid / internal graph engine

Diagram Interactivity

Each node contains:

node_id → program → section → line range


So:

Click diagram block

IDE opens correct file

Cursor jumps to exact paragraph

This satisfies your live linking requirement.

2.4 Program-Level Documentation Display

When a user clicks a program:

UI updates:

Loads program-specific .md

Shows:

Purpose

Walkthrough

Diagrams

Linked code blocks

Example interaction

Click:

Customer Menu Program


Result:

Opens customer_menu.md

Diagram + explanation

Click paragraph → opens COBOL file

2.5 Live Code Linking (Critical Feature)
How it works internally

Markdown links are not URLs, they are IDE commands:

command:vscode.open?file=customer.cbl&line=245

User experience

One click

File opens

Correct line highlighted

This creates bidirectional navigation:

Docs → Code
Code → Docs

2.6 Editable Markdown (Living Documentation)
Storage

.md files live inside the repo

Version controlled

Editing

Developers can:

Add explanations

Add business rules

Clarify logic

Safety

Swimm:

Preserves manual edits

Regenerates only machine sections

So docs don’t get overwritten.

2.7 Fast Re-Analysis Workflow

When code changes:

File watcher detects update

Only affected ASTs are rebuilt

KB is updated incrementally

Docs & diagrams refresh in seconds

This is why the video shows very fast re-analysis.

